One of these initiatives is the City Deal for Brighton and Hove, opening up &amp;pound;170m of investment, including for the Creative-Digital-IT sectors. The Deputy Prime Minister referred to our research in this announcement as evidence of the vibrant economy that was to be supported.</gtr:impact><gtr:type>Gave evidence to a government review</gtr:type></gtr:policyInfluenceOutput></gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/05FDC69B-0564-463B-ABD0-F69FDE6B6487"><gtr:id>05FDC69B-0564-463B-ABD0-F69FDE6B6487</gtr:id><gtr:title>'Creative-Digital-IT: Business Models from the Business End'</gtr:title><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/a759a64bc9aa43459d65c0bbc1581d26"><gtr:id>a759a64bc9aa43459d65c0bbc1581d26</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Sapsed, J.</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2016-01-01</gtr:date></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/1B13F9CE-E2D6-497E-86A5-4233EA345BA1"><gtr:id>1B13F9CE-E2D6-497E-86A5-4233EA345BA1</gtr:id><gtr:title>'The Business End of Business Models'</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>EGOS Annual Colloquium, 3rd-5th July, Rotterdam.</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/a759a64bc9aa43459d65c0bbc1581d26"><gtr:id>a759a64bc9aa43459d65c0bbc1581d26</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Sapsed, J.</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2014-01-01</gtr:date></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/D8FC8BF7-19EC-4776-8D0F-EE0B26A47BE8"><gtr:id>D8FC8BF7-19EC-4776-8D0F-EE0B26A47BE8</gtr:id><gtr:title>'How a New Genre is Generated'</gtr:title><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/fcbdc08943bbdec29c70858e7d8657a8"><gtr:id>fcbdc08943bbdec29c7085